# CloudFront — the CDN

Cache content close to users → most requests answered at the **edge**, not the origin.

## The network

**600+ edge locations** + **regional edge caches** (absorb misses). Request: DNS → nearest edge → **hit** returns / **miss** fetches (regional cache → origin over backbone), caches on the way back.

Also: **TLS at the edge** · free **Shield Standard** · **WAF** · HTTP/2 & 3.

## Origins & OAC

**Origin** = where CloudFront fetches on a miss (S3, ALB, EC2, any HTTP). Multiple per distribution.

**S3 origin → Origin Access Control (OAC):** bucket stays **private**, only CloudFront (SigV4) reads it. OAC replaced OAI — **default to OAC**.
